		<title>Zum Raises $100M to Expand Connected Mobility Platform</title>
		<link>https://ventureburn.com/zum-raises-100m-to-expand-connected-mobility-platform/</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Ekemini]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Thu, 16 Apr 2026 20:38:46 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Venture Capital]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://ventureburn.com/?p=200082</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>As it was establishing itself as the leader in modern student transportation, Zum announced that it is receiving a strategic investment of $100 million from TPG, allowing Zum to accelerate</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/zum-raises-100m-to-expand-connected-mobility-platform/" data-wpel-link="internal">Zum Raises $100M to Expand Connected Mobility Platform</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><span style="font-weight: 400">As it was establishing itself as the leader in modern student transportation, </span><a href="https://www.ridezum.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Zum </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">announced that it is receiving a strategic </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/spektr-secures-20m-to-transform-financial-compliance/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">investment </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">of $100 million from TPG, allowing Zum to accelerate its nationwide rollout of the Zum Connected Mobility Experience (Zum CMX&#x2122;), an integrated platform aimed at reinventing the $50 billion student mobility industry.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This latest round makes a total of $430 million raised in equity by Zum now, and the market cap estimate rises to ~1.7 billion. The raising comes on the back of an historic year for the company, which expanded operations into 17 states and now serves over 4,500 school districts, including Los Angeles Unified, San Francisco Unified, and Boston Public Schools.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Solving the &#8220;Transportation Anxiety Crisis&#8221;</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The announcement followed on the heels of a new collaborative study released by the University of Chicago’s National Opinion Research Center (NORC) in which 54% of all parents surveyed said their children &#8220;worry or are concerned about getting to school&#8221;. &#8220;Transportation anxiety&#8221; is also damaging educational progress and the nation’s bottom line, resulting in an estimated loss of 55 billion instructional minutes a year through late arrivals or non-attendance.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_200084" style="width: 410px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-200084" class="wp-image-200084" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Zum_logo_Logo.jpg" alt="Zum Logo" width="400" height="185" /><p id="caption-attachment-200084" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Zum</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">“The morning commute is the on-ramp to learning&#8221;, said Ritu Narayan, Founder and CEO of Zum. A child who gets in the car for the school day, already anxious and late, isn&#8217;t prepared to learn. With the backing of TPG, we&#8217;re expanding Zum CMX so that transportation becomes less of a barrier to education and more of a smooth, transparent, and consistent journey for every family.&#8221;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/spektr-secures-20m-to-transform-financial-compliance/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Spektr Secures $20M to Transform Financial Compliance</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">The Power of Zum CMX&#x2122;</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The core of Zum&#8217;s growth is CMX, its proprietary platform that turns bricolage and manual processes into an operating system with AML at its core. The platform combines the following:</span></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Real-Time Tracking</b><span style="font-weight: 400">: Giving our parents and administrators the ability to know where our buses are and which students have boarded them, similar to Uber.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Dynamic Routing</b><span style="font-weight: 400">: Employing artificial intelligence to plan routes daily and thus mitigating students&#8217; travel time and fuel consumption by as much as 20%.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Virtual Power Plant (VPP) Integration</b><span style="font-weight: 400">: Coadministration of Zum&#8217;s expanding fleet of electric school buses as &#8220;batteries on wheels&#8221; to feed power back into the grid on load days.</span></li>
</ul>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">A Greener, Smarter Fleet</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">But beyond logistics, Zum remains committed to its original goal of totally decarbonizing the largest mass transit system in America: the school bus. By late 2024, Zum will have helped Oakland Unified School District become the first school district in the country to operate a completely electric fleet.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">With 100 million in new capital from TPG, the company will be able to accelerate the move away from diesel and toward electric buses, taking advantage of its Vehicle-to-Grid (V2G) technology. School buses are parked up to 80% of the time, making them the backbone of a new sustainable energy ecosystem.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">With school districts nationwide facing both driver shortages and aging infrastructure, can Zum’s technology-intensive, student-first model become the new face of student transportation?</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/zum-raises-100m-to-expand-connected-mobility-platform/" data-wpel-link="internal">Zum Raises $100M to Expand Connected Mobility Platform</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
