		<title>Accel Raises $5B Fund for AI and Global Startups</title>
		<link>https://ventureburn.com/accel-raises-5b-fund/</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Ekemini]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Thu, 16 Apr 2026 18:23:40 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Venture Capital]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://ventureburn.com/?p=200074</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>Accel has closed a $5 billion fund. The new funds announced this week will be used to make high-conviction bets on AI and late-stage companies around the world, opening a</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/accel-raises-5b-fund/" data-wpel-link="internal">Accel Raises $5B Fund for AI and Global Startups</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://www.accel.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Accel </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">has closed a $5 billion </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/spektr-secures-20m-to-transform-financial-compliance/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">fund</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">. The new funds announced this week will be used to make high-conviction bets on AI and late-stage companies around the world, opening a new page for the firm that made early investments in Facebook, Spotify, and Slack.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The $5 billion will be split into two separate pools of money: $4 billion for Accel’s fifth Leaders Fund, which will be used to make growth investments, and a $650m sidecar fund, which will give limited partners the ability to scale up their investments in some of the firm&#8217;s most promising companies. The rest of the cash will be allocated to a few other focused, smaller vehicles.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">The &#8220;Portfolio That Made the Pitch&#8221;</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Accel&#8217;s newest fundraise is the latest in a series of historic outcomes in the generative AI category. Its investment in AI safety and research lab, Anthropic, has become a key part of the firm&#8217;s strategy. Accel valued Anthropic at $18.3 billion when it invested, and according to reports, in April 2026, it is said to be fielding bids for an $80 billion valuation for the company, effectively quadrupling its capital in record time.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_200075" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-200075" class="size-large wp-image-200075" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/AI-2-1024x853.jpg" alt="AI" width="1024" height="853" /><p id="caption-attachment-200075" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Unsplash</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The same is true for the firm&#8217;s investment in Cursor, an AI-native code editor. Accel led a round valuing the company at $9.9 billion, less than a year ago. Today, the firm is reportedly pushing for fresh funding at a valuation of nearly $50 billion.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">&#8220;We didn&#8217;t buy our way into the late stage; our portfolio brought us here,&#8221; said Accel Partner Matt Weigand. &#8220;As these companies scale at a breakneck pace, our late-stage fund ensures our partnership only gets stronger as they scale from startups to global behemoths.&#8221;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/spektr-secures-20m-to-transform-financial-compliance/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Spektr Secures $20M to Transform Financial Compliance</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">A Global Strategy in a Crowded Market</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The $5 billion is still a considerable sum, even if it does come into a venture market that, for the year, has already gone into overdrive. For instance, AI startups secured 297 billion dollars, the global VC total in Q1 2026.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Accel will roll out the new Leaders Fund into about 20 to 25 portfolio companies with an average check size of $200 million. &#8220;We are prepared to go much larger for &#8216;generational&#8217; companies,&#8221; said Weigand, who advised the firm would still be focused globally on an AI-powered new wave of innovation in software, robotics and defense weaponry in the US, Europe, India and Southeast Asia.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Shifting Focus to &#8220;Agentic&#8221; AI</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The additional capital will enable further penetration of AI in the transition from basic chatbots to &#8220;agentic&#8221; AI that can complete highly sophisticated workflows on its own. Accel&#8217;s portfolio already boasts pioneering companies in this space, such as Vercel, Cyera, and Mind Robotics. Accel&#8217;s focus on the &#8220;Leaders&#8221; series reflects a conviction that today&#8217;s successful entrepreneurs in AI will increase their dominance in the industry, attracting further extraordinary amounts of capital.</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/accel-raises-5b-fund/" data-wpel-link="internal">Accel Raises $5B Fund for AI and Global Startups</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
			</item>
